1
00:00:00,150 --> 00:00:00,983
- The whole point

2
00:00:00,983 --> 00:00:03,660
of relativity is to say there's
no such thing as right now

3
00:00:03,660 --> 00:00:05,520
when you're far away.

4
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:08,520
And that is doubly true for
what's inside a black hole.

5
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:10,920
And you might think, well,
the galaxy is very big.

6
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:12,000
It's really not.

7
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,110
It's some tens of thousands
of light years across

8
00:00:16,110 --> 00:00:18,420
and billions of years old.

9
00:00:18,420 --> 00:00:20,840
So you don't need to
move at a high fraction

10
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:23,310
of the speed of light to fill the galaxy.

11
00:00:23,310 --> 00:00:26,070
- The number of worlds is-

12
00:00:26,070 --> 00:00:26,903
- [Sean] Very big.

13
00:00:26,903 --> 00:00:29,820
- Very, very, very big.

14
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:32,790
Where do those worlds fit?

15
00:00:32,790 --> 00:00:34,050
Where they go?

16
00:00:34,050 --> 00:00:35,403
- The short answer is,

17
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:40,473
the worlds don't exist in space.

18
00:00:41,490 --> 00:00:45,633
Space exists separately in each world.

